{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c266fc08-e51f-430b-89c5-0ee8574b16d7","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8876bbea-e97f-404a-94db-484bec2129c6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"0BD8:38E18D:3BC0AE:459F20:69F00CBE"},"id":"a285ef19-353c-439c-a674-42148f6f71a8","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:26:26.123Z","parentId":"fe69296c-8bdd-414e-a563-0f522409b228"}
